  "text": "Compared with other inhibitors of HPV infection (5, 9), K5 derivatives can be tailored in structure and molecular weight to closely mimic cell surface HSPG to reach high and specific affinities for the HPV capsid. Unlike heparin, they are devoid of anticoagulant activity [CITATION_1] , and since their structure is very similar to natural HS, they are metabolically recognized and easily catabolized; therefore, no toxicity is expected. Moreover, recent results from whole-blood assays to detect proinflammatory activity showed that neither cytokines nor chemokines were mobilized in the presence of K5 derivatives (E. Vincenzi, personal communication).",
